theorem ideal.inter_add_mem {I J : Ideal R} {a b : R} (ha : a ∈ I ∩ J) (hb : b ∈ I ∩ J) : a + b ∈ I ∩ J := by
  have haI : a ∈ I := ha.1
  have haJ : a ∈ J := ha.2
  have hbI : b ∈ I := hb.1
  have hbJ : b ∈ J := hb.2
  
  have habI : a + b ∈ I := I.add_mem haI hbI
  have habJ : a + b ∈ J := J.add_mem haJ hbJ
  
  exact ⟨habI, habJ⟩
```

This proof directly shows that if `a` and `b` are in both `I` and `J`, then `a + b` is in both `I` and `J` because `I` and `J` are closed under addition. 

